 temperatures\nof superclusters are predicted without any adjustable parameter using a sample\nvolume varying by nearly 18 orders of magnitude. The classical Gibbs free\nenergy change is used, adding an enthalpy saving related to the Laplace\npressure change associated with supercluster formation, which is quantified and\nstrongly weakened for n = 13 and 55.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Apr 2014 05:16:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 25 Apr 2014 14:42:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 28 Jul 2014 13:31:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-29"}
